Cyber Claw:







Two green peircing eyes spied out from the forest, watching two creatures 
pass in the distance. One was a raptor, almost like her, and the other was a 
flying panther.

She snarled with her mouth gaped. All of her teeth were exposed. She was 
angry, two bots had trespassed into her territory. She spread her three 
digit fingers from behind the vegiation.

The raptor moved off like a shadow, keeping down wind. She knew how to 
survive here. As far as she was concerned, she was a child of the wild, not 
brought on-line to it, but forced to live by it. She betrayed her leader, 
and this is what she got. She was a clone, but she no longer cared. She was 
who she was. Try to change it, she couldn't. She was a female version of a 
male warrior. She was an assissin. Well built, with many talents.

She watched them, traling them as if she was a harmless shadow. When the 
time was perfect, she would kill them.
